
MiniJukebox
-----------

MiniJukebox started out as a oneliner (see the archive directory) and then later changed into a
rather small commandline frontend for the WinAmp Radio streams website. Probably there are many
easier ways to surf and get those radio channels but just for the fun of a hack I created this.


Features
--------

  o Caching of results into binary blobs for later use
  o Time measurement of the stream speeds via libcurl


Depends
-------

  o Ruby
  o Ruby HPricot
  o Mplayer
  o curl (for the -t option)


Todo
----

  o Make a nice configuration file to choose, e.g. which player to use etc.
    (default is currently mplayer)
  o Threads (e.g. 5 simulat. access to the website)

Usage
-----

% ./MiniJukebox.rb -h
/usr/lib/ruby/1.8/hpricot/builder.rb:11: warning: `&' interpreted as argument prefix
Usage: minijukebox [options]
    -o, --usecache                   Use the already cached Playlist
    -r, --recache                    Recache the Playlist *now*
    -v, --[no-]verbose               Run verbosely
    -t, --time                       Benchmark all streams


Just run ./MiniJukebox and enjoy.


